1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3592 By: Lepak
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to Medicaid; defining term;
prohibiting Medicaid funds for abortions; permitting
8 exceptions; providing for codification; and providing
an effective date.
9
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-729.10 of Title 63, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. As used in this section, "Abortion" shall have the same
17 meaning as defined in section 1-730 of this title.
18 B. No Medicaid or SoonerCare funds shall be paid to an entity,
19 including its affiliates, subsidiaries, successors, or clinics, that
20 is primarily engaged in family planning services, reproductive
21 health, and related medical care that provides for abortions, other
22 than an abortion:
23 1. In the case where the pregnancy is the result of an act of
24 rape or incest; or
Req. No. 15165 Page 1

1 2. In the case where a woman suffers from a physical disorder,
2 physical injury, or physical illness, including a life-endangering
3 physical condition caused by or arising from the pregnancy itself,
4 that would, as certified by a physician, place the woman in danger
5 of death unless an abortion is performed.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
